text: I told my computer I needed a break, and it replied, 'Ctrl+Alt+Delete your stress!'
Parallel lines have so much in common, but they'll never meet.
I used to be a baker, but I couldn't make enough dough.
I'm reading a book on anti-gravity; it's impossible to put down!
I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high; she looked surprised.
I'm on a seafood diet: I see food, and I eat it!
I tried to catch fog, but I mist.
I told my friend she drew her eyeliner too thick; she said it was her bold look!
I used to play piano by ear, but now I use my hands.
I'm friends with all my clocks; we always have a great time!
I told my dog he’s a good boy, and now he’s wagging his tail off!
I got a job at a bakery because I kneaded the cash.
I tried to write a joke about time travel, but it hasn't landed yet.
I wanted to be a motivational speaker, but I kept losing my train of thought.
My cat just walked across my keyboard; now my essay is pawsitively ruined!
I told my lamp it was too bright; it dimmed its enthusiasm.
I tried to organize a space party, but the aliens were too spaced out.
I asked my mirror for advice, but it just reflected my bad decisions.
I bought a new vacuum; it really sucks at everything!
I told my fridge to chill, and now it’s giving me the cold shoulder.
I tried to join a choir, but they said I was too pitchy.
I asked my phone for directions, but it just kept ringing off the hook.
I told my chair to take a seat, but it just stood there.
I tried to befriend a cloud, but it kept raining on my parade.
My calendar is so full, it’s practically dated!
I told my pencil it was pointless, and it broke under pressure.
I tried to cook dinner, but my kitchen said, 'You're out of thyme!'
I asked my shoes for a walk, but they were too tied up.
I told my pillow I needed rest, and it said, 'Dream on!'
I tried to learn coding, but I kept getting stuck in a loop.
I told my coffee it was brewed perfectly, and it perked up!
I asked my plant for growth advice, but it just leafed me alone.
I tried to write a novel, but I kept getting writer’s block.
I told my car it was tired, and it replied, 'I'm exhausted!'
I asked my clock for a second, and it ticked me off.
I tried to dance with my broom, but it swept me off my feet.
I told my socks they were a great pair, and they got all warm and fuzzy.
I asked my hat to cover for me, but it just sat there.
I tried to tell a chemistry joke, but there was no reaction.
I told my ladder it was a step up, and it climbed with confidence.
I asked my wallet for cash, but it was empty-handed.
I tried to tell a light bulb joke, but it wasn’t very bright.
I told my dog he was fetching, and he brought me a stick.
I asked my window for a view, but it just gave me a pane.
I tried to make a pun about wind, but it blew away.
I told my guitar it was out of tune, and it strung me along.
I asked my door to open up, but it stayed closed-off.
I tried to tell a math joke, but it didn’t add up.
I told my candle it was lit, and it glowed with pride.
I asked my fan to cool it, and it spun out of control.
